article.headline: Lafayette 77, Binghamton 72
article.story: EASTON, Pa. (AP) -- Justin DeBerry and Sean Kittner hit back-to-back 3-pointers late in the game to seal a 77-72 victory over Binghamton on Sunday. Leading by one, DeBerry hit a 3, then called timeout while falling out of bounds after recovering a blocked shot at the other end. On the ensuing possession, Kittner nailed a 3 to open up a 72-65 lead for the Leopards. DeBerry finished with 19 points and seven rebounds. Kittner added 15 points for Lafayette (5-1). Binghamton (3-4) was led by Nick Billings, who had a career-high 21 points and seven rebounds. Winston Davis scored 16 points for Lafayette, shooting 4-7 from beyond the 3-point line. For Binghamton, Troy Hailey added 14 points, Alex Adediran had 11 and Sebastian Hermenier had 10. The Leopards are off until Dec. 17, when they host Lycoming. Binghamton visits defending national champion Syracuse on Saturday.
